<h3><span class="editsection">[<a href="/w/index.php?title=Irish_language&amp;action=edit&amp;section=27" title="Edit section: Grammar and pronunciation">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline" id="Grammar_and_pronunciation">Grammar and pronunciation</span></h3>
<ul>
<li><a href="http://en.wikisource.org/wiki/en:A_dialect_of_Donegal" class="extiw" title="s:en:A dialect of Donegal"><i>A dialect of Donegal</i></a> (a phonological description of the dialect of <a href="/wiki/Glenties" title="Glenties">Glenties</a> by E.&#160;C. Quiggin, from 1906)</li>
<li><a href="http://www.angaelmagazine.com/pronunciation/introduction.htm" class="external text" rel="nofollow">An Gael Magazine</a> - Irish Gaelic Arts, Culture, And History Alive Worldwide Today</li>
<li><a href="http://www.miejipang-jpn2.net/untitled3.html" class="external text" rel="nofollow">A short Irish and Breton phrase list with Japanese translation(Renewal)</a> incl sound file</li>
<li><a href="http://nualeargais.ie/gnag/gram.htm" class="external text" rel="nofollow">Braesicke's Gramadach na Gaeilge (Engl. translation)</a></li>
<li><a href="http://en.wikisource.org/wiki/de:Die_araner_mundart" class="extiw" title="s:de:Die araner mundart"><i>Die araner mundart</i></a> (a phonological description of the dialect of the <a href="/wiki/Aran_Islands" title="Aran Islands">Aran Islands</a> by F.&#160;N. Finck, from 1899)</li>
</ul>
